                                                                      "line":  20,
                                                                      "body":  "**\u003csub\u003e\u003csub\u003e![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)\u003c/sub\u003e\u003c/sub\u003e  Gate release creation on successful publishing**\n\nWhen a release tag points at a commit whose `sdk/pyproject.toml` version matches but the separate `.github/workflows/publish.yml` job later fails its lint/tests/release-guard/build/PyPI upload, this workflow still creates the public GitHub Release because both workflows are independent `push`-tag triggers with no `needs`/`workflow_run` ordering. That can leave users and the release-content links pointing at an announced version that is not actually installable from PyPI.\n\nUseful? React with 👍 / 👎.",
                                                                      "author":  {
                                                                                     "login":  "chatgpt-codex-connector"
                                                                                 },
                                                                      "url":  "https://github.com/bmdhodl/agent47/pull/520#discussion_r3308466147",
                                                                      "createdAt":  "2026-05-27T04:34:40Z"
                                                                  }
                                                              ]
                                                }
                               },
                               {
                                   "id":  "PRRT_kwDORIKzHM6E_uCN",
